  "original_title": "\u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd2 \u0db8\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dc0\u0dd3\u0db8 \u0db1\u0dc0\u0dad\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Stops milk churning",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Minister of Agriculture Mahinda Amaraweera has instructed that the National Livestock Development Board and Milko institutes stop the production of skimmed milk and give priority to other milk-related products including liquid milk, powdered milk.",
        "As the amount of milk received by the two companies has decreased and the import of milk-related products has been suspended, the minister's instructions state that priority should not be given to the production of skimmed milk and instead priority should be given to other milk-related products.",
        "The Ministry of Agriculture says that due to the shortage of animal feed in the country, the production of liquid milk has dropped by about 34 percent.",
        "Currently, the two companies NLDB and Milko produce many milk-related products, including powdered milk, liquid milk, cheese, butter, skimmed milk and flavored liquid milk and ice cream.",
        "Since the production of skimmed milk is a cottage industry, the country has enough skimmed milk and advised the two companies to take such measures to avoid a shortage of other milk-related products in the market.",
        "The Minister informed this in a discussion held with the National Livestock Board and Milko Company, Minister of Agriculture, Mr. Mahinda Amaraweera."
      ],
